content:
This service lets you create and update a set of products and their content.

The set is products is hierarchical in nature. For example, if you have a shirt that comes in 3 colors and 5 sizes per color, you would normally define a root product that then contains the 3 color products
and each color product would contain the 5 different sizes, which would be the SKU. How you define the hierarchy is up to you, it's also fine to have the 3 color products as root products and only have them
contain the SKUs, or to forego a hierarchy entirely and just create the SKUs, but creating the root and color products is useful for search and frontend purposes.


An example request of a hierarchy:

{
  "ID": "special_shirt",
  "Name": "Special Shirt",
  "TaxCode": "High",
  "Variations": {
    "Property": "color_code",
    "LogicalLevel": "color",
    "Products": [
      {
        "ID": "special_shirt_blue",
        "Name": "Special Shirt - Blue",
        "VariationValues": [
          {
            "LanguageID": null,
            "Value": "BLUE"
          }
        ],
        "Variations": {
          "Property": "size_code",
          "LogicalLevel": "size",
          "Products": [
            {
              "ID": "sku_special_shirt_blue_xl",
              "VariationValues": [
                {
                  "LanguageID": null,
                  "Value": "XL"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}

